#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn51.33-44"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn51.33-44:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 51 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 51 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.33-44:0.2"
msgid "4. Gaṅgāpeyyālavagga "
msgstr "4. Abbreviated Texts on the Ganges "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn51.33-44:0.3"
msgid "33–44. Gaṅgānadīādisutta "
msgstr "33–44. The Ganges River, Etc. "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn51.33-44:1.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gaṅgā nadī pācīnaninnā pācīnapoṇā pācīnapabbhārā; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, the Ganges river slants, slopes, and inclines to the east. "

msgctxt "sn51.33-44:1.2"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro iddhipāde bhāvento cattāro iddhipāde bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro. "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant who develops and cultivates the four bases of psychic power slants, slopes, and inclines to extinguishment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.33-44:1.3"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro iddhipāde bhāvento cattāro iddhipāde bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro? "
msgstr "And how does a mendicant who develops the four bases of psychic power slant, slope, and incline to extinguishment? "

msgctxt "sn51.33-44:1.4"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti, "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm … "

msgctxt "sn51.33-44:1.5"
msgid "vīriyasamādhi … pe … "
msgstr "energy … "

msgctxt "sn51.33-44:1.6"
msgid "cittasamādhi … "
msgstr "mental development … "

msgctxt "sn51.33-44:1.7"
msgid "vīmaṃsāsamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "inquiry, and active effort. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.291, sc2
msgctxt "sn51.33-44:2.1"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro iddhipāde bhāvento cattāro iddhipāde bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro”ti. "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant who develops and cultivates the four bases of psychic power slants, slopes, and inclines to extinguishment.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn51.33-44:2.2"
msgid "Dvādasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn51.33-44:2.3"
msgid "Gaṅgāpeyyālavaggo catuttho. "
msgstr "(To be expanded for each of the different rivers as in SN 45.91–102.) "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn51.33-44:3.1"
msgid "Cha pācīnato ninnā, "
msgstr "Six on slanting to the east, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn51.33-44:3.2"
msgid "cha ninnā ca samuddato; "
msgstr "and six on slanting to the ocean; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn51.33-44:3.3"
msgid "Dvete cha dvādasa honti, "
msgstr "these two sixes make twelve, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn51.33-44:3.4"
msgid "vaggo tena pavuccatīti. "
msgstr "and that’s how this chapter is recited."

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
